	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">J2 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">He said that he didn't like the CHR bankswitching for sprites or something. ie, he wanted to bankswitch sprites in less than 1KB chunks</div>
<br />The Final Fantasy games for Famicom used VRAM for fine-grained bankswitching. For something more graphically intense, I think someone needs to make a mapper that allows arbitrary writes to VRAM through a latch that sneaks them into the cycles when the PPU isn't accessing memory. First proposal was <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=106" class="postlink">here</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


